Faced with European opposition, Germany is beginning to speculate about three possible ways out of the crisis.
The first is a strong euro area, which would include Germany, but also Austria and the Netherlands, while the southern states would leave the currency zone.
The second is the return to the mark - although it may now appear to be a scifi, this version has broad public support, approaching 50% of the population.
The third option, according to Germany's proposals, is to redecorate the euro with greater macroeconomic supervision, budgetary rigour, fines for the guilty states, possible deferrals for some of them, and to extend the possible costs of regulation to the private sector.
