Provoking a yellow card under similar conditions is not a new practice, but is more or less common in football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos of football, that is, rules that are unwritten, but watch each other.
Part of the discussion in this case was due to the fact that the Real Madrid team (who boasts generosity and honour in his anthem and who has already fined his players for similar acts) and, it seems, also thanks to the drama led by Mourinh, which adds another episode to his long history of comedian and provocateur.
in any case, the debate revolves around whether this kind of action, which is not explicitly prohibited by the rules, is contrary to the principles of sport, that is to say, whether there is circumvention of the law in these acts; indeed, it is actions that respect sports rules, which, of course, seem to be trying to circumvent.
It addresses the type of damage such acts cause to the sports spirit.
One of the elements of sport behavior is the physical integrity of opponents, which has not been violated in these cases, so there has been no violent play.
Another of these elements characterizing a clean game is to avoid players having an advantage against the opponent's team because of their offense - which also did not happen here.
So the paradoxical thing about Real Madrid players' action is that what we normally characterize as a ruse or circumvention of the law did not occur, there was no hidden violation of the rules in order to avoid penalty, but this behavior should have been as obvious as possible in order to receive the penalty.
They waited and were happy to receive the punishment.
Another question, however, is what advantage the guilty will have from their intentional transgression.
It is necessary to state here that the opponent is not in a disadvantaged position and that in the current match there is no benefit, because the obvious consequence is that the team will have fewer players.
