So as the wheels continue, it will not be clear whether this is an advantage.
In short, these negotiations do not go against the sport spirit, which includes making strategic decisions that allow maximum benefit to be gained under the rules.
in the case we are dealing with here, the goal was not to avoid the granting of punishment (which would be a clear case of circumvention), but rather to choose when to submit to it.
They made a strategic decision without avoiding or running from punishment.
Although the line between ingenuity and circumvention is not clear, I believe that in this case it was clearly a wit.
